      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/01/like-a-charm/#comment-9277"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-01-21T22:01:00-05:00">Monday, January 21, 2008 at 10:01 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>You are so right in that the weather here in Seattle is off to sort a great start. Today in West Seattle, it is very nice out and as yours, my italian parsley is booming! I have made parsley pesto with great success. I also make a nage(broth) as well to accompany fish or vegetable dishes. Hand chop parsley leaves, reduce some vegetable or chicken stock with shallots, mushroom stems, vermouth, and parsley stems. Reduce by half. Strain, and then whisk in the parsley leaves, minced preserved lemon, butter and evoo. Season. Great with steamed or poached fish, gnocchi etc. It&#8217;s use in pasta doughs works well also. Time to pick some rosemary blossoms for that tea of yours. check out my blog when you can&#8230;cuisinierskitchen.blogspot.com </>cuisinier</p>
    </div>

